I just completed an intense engineering course, learning how to develop software for self-driving cars, to enable reactions as though a human were in control. This was one of the most challenging programs I have ever experienced. The curriculum involved 14 projects.

11 months of concentration provided a wealth of knowledge across a spectrum of advanced areas including computer vision, deep learning, sensor fusion, localization, control, path planning, functional safety, and system integration using Python, C++, TensorFlow, and ROS.

The final project involved forming an international team. The code we developed successfully controlled a Lincoln MKZ around a closed-circuit test track in Palo Alto, California. Even with the sun glaring on dashboard camera images, the system successfully obeyed traffic light signals and navigated a prescribed path. My team, the “level5-engineers”, includes James (lead), Aman, Yousof, and Rajesh .
I graduated and now hold a Nanodegree as a self-driving car engineer. Udacity has changed my life and I'm grateful to my instructors, mentors including Sebastian, David and all fellow cohorts.
5 months of hard-work and persistence finally pays off.
